(8075, 412, 'description', 'As the Director of Finance, Mrs. Shaver oversees all financial aspects SETA International Group.<br> \r\n<br>\r\nMrs. Shaver was previously the CFO at D/K Technologies which grew a network of international distributors and suppliers.  With it came challenges that each business experiences, capital equipment purchases, keeping supply in a timely manner  employee management/cash flow management. The company realized sustained growth under her leadership, doubling sales from 1998-2005.<br>\r\n<br>\r\nMrs. Shaver holds a Bachelors Degree from California State University Long Beach.\r\n\r\n'),
(6682, 77, 'image', '1376840181icon_leader01.png'),
(8047, 77, 'description', 'Mr. Cranney oversees all strategic business development and sales strategy for SETA International Ireland. Mr. Cranney is an innovative, energetic and hands-on senior IT leader with 15 years international experience successfully developing and delivering value-orientated solutions to meet business needs through the practical application of technology. He has the ability to quickly identify and architect solutions due to strong technical background and has a strong track record of developing and managing applications and projects. He collaborates with senior management on future strategies, investment decisions and solution selections. Starting as a graduate software developer, Mr. Cranney has worked globally in roles of increasing responsibility, most recently as a Global IT Director with Celestica reporting to the CIO, before joining SETA International.<br>\r\n<br>\r\nMr. Cranney holds a BSc. in Software Engineering from Queens University in Belfast, Ireland.'),
(6688, 75, 'image', '1376840076icon_leader01.png'),
(8079, 75, 'description', 'As the head of SETA International KK Japan, Mr. Hirose assumes the role of CEO/President of one of SETA International''s global offices in Tokyo, Japan. Mr. Hirose is responsible for the companys strategic direction spanning across sales, business development, marketing, operations and development. With over 20+ years in the technology industry, Mr. Hirose brings a wealth of industry knowledge and a thorough understanding of sales and marketing to SETA International KK. Since 1991.<br>\r\n<br>\r\nMr. Hirose has held various executive positions at companies including Mitsubishi, Cisco, MSC Software and Terras and played a major role in the growth of the companies. Mr. Hirose is a graduate of the University computer expert.'),
(6795, 76, 'image', '1376840143icon_leader01.png'),
(6796, 76, 'description', 'Mr. Ho oversees all day-to-day activities including project delivery, financial management and technical operations of the companys delivery center in Vietnam. He is instrumental in providing overall direction to and leadership of the engineering teams at SETA International''s technology centers worldwide.<br>\r\n<br>\r\nMr. Ho is a graduate of the Hanoi University of Science and Technology.'),
(6696, 424, '_thumbnail_id', '423'),
(6790, 424, 'description', 'As the head of operations for SETA International Vietnam, Vu is responsible for over 200+ employees ranging from software developers, quality assurance engineers and project managers. Mr. Vu has experience running global operations for a number of top IT firms in Vietnam and held a number of executive positions reporting to companies in the US, Canada and the UK.<br>\r\n<br>\r\nMr. Vu holds a BS of Computer Science from the Hanoi University of Science and Technology and a PhD of Computer Science from the University of New South Wales, Australia.'),
