(7405, 492, 'description', '<p>Gulliver operates in the used car distribution business. We have grown based on an original business model of selling cars purchased by our approximately 420 directly managed and franchised stores across Japan at auction rather than using showrooms, within seven to ten days of their purchase. Formerly, used car businesses maintained showrooms and incurred the associated inventory risk and display costs. Through selling cars quickly at auction, Gulliver has been able to reduce its inventory risk and eliminate display costs. By shortening the time from purchase to sale, we have created a profitable, low cost operation where lower gross margins are offset by the large numbers of cars handled.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>SETA has entered into a formal agreement with Gulliver Interational to assist with their product development roadmap. SETA is also working closely with Gulliver to augment their internal staff by bringing on SETA''s top quality software developers and quality assurance engineers to help maximize efficiency and productivity. Once Gulliver integrated SETA''s industry leading hybrid development model, they were able to quickly achieve efficiency across their software development organization while reducing operational cost and maximizing ROI.</p>'),
